%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: The_blaze_of_life_can_reap_just_the_same
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 85
  mythName: The blaze of life can reap just the same
  omens:
  - '1. A field of golden flowers, moles-a-brightly

    munching on their stems.
    The Sun

    appears extra bright, even peeking over

    the horizon at night.'
  - '2. A couple, vagabonds living off the land,

    carrying a basket of fruit.
    They praise the

    Sun for an unusually ripe bounty.

    Immediately flee
    from the Knights.'
  - '3. The Sun rises to new heights, not setting

    again until the Myth is resolved.
    Roll a

    new blessing of the Sun each time you

    arrive at a settlement
    (see opposite).'
  - '4. A shady grotto, 5 raiders arguing loudly

    within. They are frustrated
    that they

    cannot raid at night anymore. They plan

    a dire attack on
    the nearest Holding.'
  - '5. A drought on the land. Wells dry, ground

    hardens, rivers die. The Sun
    brings no

    more boons, only banes.'
  - '6. The Sun swells further, then descends on

    the Realm in the form of the
    feaster, a

    colossal golden man. He bounds about the

    Realm eating anything
    that grows.

    Terrified of animals, but not humans.'
  verse: 'Omens

    1. A field of golden flowers, moles-a-brightly

    munching
    on their stems. The Sun

    appears extra bright, even peeking over

    the
    horizon at night.

    2. A couple, vagabonds living off the land,

    carrying
    a basket of fruit. They praise the

    Sun for an unusually ripe bounty.

    Immediately
    flee from the Knights.

    3. The Sun rises to new heights, not setting

    again
    until the Myth is resolved. Roll a

    new blessing of the Sun each time you

    arrive
    at a settlement (see opposite).

    4. A shady grotto, 5 raiders arguing loudly

    within.
    They are frustrated that they

    cannot raid at night anymore. They plan

    a
    dire attack on the nearest Holding.

    5. A drought on the land. Wells dry,
    ground

    hardens, rivers die. The Sun brings no

    more boons, only banes.

    6.
    The Sun swells further, then descends on

    the Realm in the form of the feaster,
    a

    colossal golden man. He bounds about the

    Realm eating anything that
    grows.

    Terrified of animals, but not humans.

    Cast

    The Sun, in
    the Form of the Feaster

    VIG 18, CLA 5, SPI 10, 4 GD

    A6 (colossal body)

    Crush
    (2d12 or d12 blast)

    Wants to eat all crops. Afraid of animals.

    Mole-a-Brightly,
    Blazenose

    VIG 3, CLA 13, SPI 2, 3 GD

    Glows pleasantly when eating,
    hates that

    which it does not already know.

    Raiders, Opal and Company

    VIG
    12, CLA 12, SPI 7, 3 GD

    Hatchet (d6), bow (d6 long), stolen trinkets

    Vagabond
    Couple, Harnis & Raschle

    VIG 9, CLA 14, SPI 12, 2 GD

    Dagger (d6), sling
    (d6), distrust Knights

    Aurant of crown, a sov''reign aflame'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Sun, in the Form of the Feaster
    statBlock: 'VIG 18, CLA 5, SPI 10, 4 GD

      A6 (colossal body)'
    notes: 'Crush (2d12 or d12 blast)

      Wants to eat all crops. Afraid of animals.'
  - name: Mole-a-Brightly, Blazenose
    statBlock: 'VIG 3, CLA 13, SPI 2, 3 GD

      Glows pleasantly when eating, hates
      that'
    notes: which it does not already know.
  - name: Raiders, Opal and Company
    statBlock: 'VIG 12, CLA 12, SPI 7, 3 GD

      Hatchet (d6), bow (d6 long), stolen
      trinkets'
    notes: 
  - name: Vagabond Couple, Harnis & Raschle
    statBlock: 'VIG 9, CLA 14, SPI 12, 2 GD

      Dagger (d6), sling (d6), distrust
      Knights'
    notes: 'Aurant of crown, a sov''reign aflame

      The blaze of life can reap
      just the same

      BLESSINGS OF THE SUN

      Boon Bane

      1 Early harvest
      Forest fire

      2 Huge ball game Exhausted elders

      3 Outdoor performance
      Worn out steeds

      4 Choir of birds Ruined cropfield

      5 Travelling
      merchants Insect swarms

      6 Day of rest proclaimed Desperate predators

      Sun

      Dwelling:
      Signal tower ~ Sanctum: Shady grotto ~ Monument: Sun brazier

      Hazard:
      Stinging swarms ~ Curse: Foul shadow ~ Ruin: Dirge-horn altar

      Th'
  flavorTable:
    title: BLESSINGS OF THE SUN
    rows:
    - 1 Early harvest Forest fire
    - 2 Huge ball game Exhausted elders
    - 3 Outdoor performance Worn out steeds
    - 4 Choir of birds Ruined cropfield
    - 5 Travelling merchants Insect swarms
    - '6 Day of rest proclaimed Desperate predators

      Sun'
  dwelling: Signal tower
  sanctum: Shady grotto
  monument: Sun brazier
  hazard: Stinging swarms
  curse: Foul shadow
  ruin: Dirge-horn altar
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
